<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <title>Ruby in the Cloud</title>

        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no">
        <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">

        <link href="sdx/css/sdx.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
        <style>
            .sub-title {
                margin-bottom: 0;
            }
            .code-block {
                background-color: #333;
                color: #F8FAFB;
                padding: 1em;
                overflow-x: scroll;
            }
            .code-block p {
                font-family: monospace;
                font-size: 0.8em;
                margin-bottom: -0.2em;
            }
            .code-block span {
                color: #BBB;
            }
            .tech-icon {
                height: 3em;
                margin-bottom: 1em;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="page">
            <div class="container">

                <div class="margin-v-4">
                    <img alt="Ruby" src="images/ruby.svg" class="tech-icon">
                    <h1>This is Ruby in the Cloud!</h1>
                    <p>Congratulations! You successfully pushed a Ruby app into the cloud.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="card card--dark card--notification card--blue card--not-rounded">
                    <div class="card__header">
                        <h1 class="align-left">Getting Started</h1>
                    </div>
                    <p class="card__text">To push your own source code, either upload it as a ZIP file to the web console or use the <a href="https://github.com/cloudfoundry/cli#downloads">cf CLI</a> instead.</p>
                    <p class="card__text"><a href="https://docs.developer.swisscom.com/tutorial-ruby/">This tutorial</a> will get you started on the whole process.</p>
                </div>

                <br>

                <% unless @env_variables.empty? %>
                    <div class="margin-v-4">
                        <h3 class="sub-title">Environment Variables</h3>
                        <pre class="code-block"><% @env_variables.each do |key, val| %><p><%= key %>: <span><%= val %></span></p><% end %></pre>
                    </div>
                <% end %>

                <% unless @req_headers.empty? %>
                    <div class="margin-v-4">
                        <h3 class="sub-title">Request Headers</h3>
                        <pre class="code-block"><% @req_headers.each do |key, val| %><p><%= key %>: <span><%= val %></span></p><% end %></pre>
                    </div>
                <% end %>

                <% unless @req_params.empty? %>
                    <div class="margin-v-4">
                        <h3 class="sub-title">Request Parameters</h3>
                        <pre class="code-block"><% @req_params.each do |key, val| %><p><%= key %>: <span><%= val %></span></p><% end %></pre>
                    </div>
                <% end %>


            </div>
        </div>

